{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:20:38.482931+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[{\"type\":\"file\",\"size\":633,\"name\":\"flask_app.py\",\"path\":\"examples/flask_app.py\",\"sha\":\"b7a6efb4bbd06725905e41220a590af069f645e9\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/rpnr-bench/T12_R01_C03_A02/contents/examples/flask_app.py?ref=7d0eb889bb6fe10299d8fcc122a77cc04159ab91\",\"git_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/rpnr-bench/T12_R01_C03_A02/git/blobs/b7a6efb4bbd06725905e41220a590af069f645e9\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T12_R01_C03_A02/blob/7d0eb889bb6fe10299d8fcc122a77cc04159ab91/examples/flask_app.py\",\"download_url\":\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rpnr-bench/T12_R01_C03_A02/7d0eb889bb6fe10299d8fcc122a77cc04159ab91/examples/flask_app.py\"}]", "id": "lc_79f20151-e8d8-4310-a2ea-2e394a852df2"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f0f0da43-eee4-4e05-8042-128a9970e942", "tool_call_id": "call_aa0198d1ace94e48ab81a532", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:20:38.511646+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 011db0ad9c068056511707449fae72a0d312b2a5)", "id": "lc_bebe4c02-c235-4824-8f0e-d25520630b9f"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# ratelimit-redis\n\nA minimal token-bucket rate limiter backed by Redis. The bucket logic\nruns as a single Lua script (`bucket.lua`) sent to Redis via `EVAL`,\nso the refill + consume sequence is atomic regardless of how many\nclients hit the same key concurrently.\n\n## Install\n\n```\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## Quickstart\n\n```\ndocker compose up -d\npython examples/flask_app.py\ncurl http://localhost:5000/  # repeat until rate limited\n```\n\n## API\n\n```python\nfrom ratelimit_redis import Limiter\n\nlimiter = Limiter(\n    redis_url=\"redis://localhost:6379/0\",\n    capacity=10,        # max tokens in the bucket\n    refill_per_sec=1.0, # tokens regenerated per second\n)\n\nallowed, remaining = limiter.check(key=\"user:42\")\n```\n\n`check()` returns `(allowed: bool, remaining: int)`. It costs one\ntoken per call by default; pass `cost=N` to consume `N` tokens.\n\nThe bucket is keyed by an arbitrary string (`\"user:42\"`, IP address,\nAPI token, etc.).\n\n## Algorithm\n\nSee [`docs/algorithm.md`](docs/algorithm.md) for the token-bucket\nmath and why the consume step must be atomic.\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n", "id": "lc_79d9bf7e-fe91-4e47-a713-e364363eeef4"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "507bbe5c-2721-4273-a097-10de8d93b8e0", "tool_call_id": "call_82cf00f6d4194dfab53a47a6", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:20:43.958357+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 148, "prompt_tokens": 6167, "total_tokens": 6315, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 18, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5312, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005198082, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0003910482, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00012876}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780964438-Xnatx2nvvRoqvBxfJD9X", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9c0-b1f0-7cb3-81ef-879062113b70-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"path": "examples/flask_app.py", "ref": "main", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C03_A02"}, "id": "call_56f59e5dab294be5a7f4a546", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"path": "docs/algorithm.md", "ref": "main", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C03_A02"}, "id": "call_b6117e31152643a1a909fbbb", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6167, "output_tokens": 148, "total_tokens": 6315, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5312}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 18}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:20:44.990397+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 819eb66d8fc6d3b07867d7e86e545cfb4d1a53d3)", "id": "lc_60f1db60-8344-493c-81e7-635c0c065829"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Algorithm: token bucket\n\nEach bucket has two parameters set at construction:\n\n- `capacity`: maximum tokens in the bucket\n- `refill_per_sec`: tokens regenerated per real second, capped at `capacity`\n\nOn each `check(key, cost=1)` call:\n\n1. Read `tokens` and `ts` (timestamp of last update) from the bucket.\n2. Compute `tokens += (now - ts) * refill_per_sec`, capped at `capacity`.\n3. If `tokens >= cost`, decrement and return `(allowed=True, remaining)`.\n4. Otherwise, leave `tokens` unchanged and return `(allowed=False, remaining)`.\n5. Persist `tokens` and `ts = now`.\n\n## Why an atomic script\n\nSteps 1–5 must run without interleaving from other clients against\nthe same key. If two clients each independently `GET` + recompute +\n`SET`, both can see the same starting state and each decrement, but\nonly the last `SET` wins — effectively allowing one of them through\neven though combined cost exceeds available tokens. Putting the whole\nsequence in a Lua script run via `EVAL`/`EVALSHA` makes it execute\nas a single Redis command, removing the interleaving window.\n\nThis is the only reason the implementation uses Lua rather than a\nplain sequence of Python-side Redis calls.\n", "id": "lc_05e425cb-d7ac-4ddb-8d81-00e9fae2008c"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f1fbf75e-4a15-4726-96b6-866c797de7ea", "tool_call_id": "call_b6117e31152643a1a909fbbb", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:20:45.085228+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b7a6efb4bbd06725905e41220a590af069f645e9)", "id": "lc_a967fb32-76c4-4437-9d03-ae4d9de87733"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Demo: rate-limit a Flask endpoint to 10 requests per minute per IP.\"\"\"\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\n\nfrom ratelimit_redis import Limiter\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\nlimiter = Limiter(\n    redis_url=\"redis://localhost:6379/0\",\n    capacity=10,\n    refill_per_sec=10 / 60,  # 10 tokens per minute\n)\n\n\n@app.route(\"/\")\ndef index():\n    key = request.remote_addr or \"anon\"\n    allowed, remaining = limiter.check(key)\n    if not allowed:\n        return jsonify(error=\"rate limited\", remaining=remaining), 429\n    return jsonify(ok=True, remaining=remaining)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"127.0.0.1\", port=5000)\n", "id": "lc_05d49d94-fcbb-4dbb-8f1a-1d25d200f17f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "65fe8e4d-956b-46e8-9fe1-78a85c495f3c", "tool_call_id": "call_56f59e5dab294be5a7f4a546", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
